or%20so-called%20%26quot%3Bknowledge%20workers%2C%26quot%3B%20choose%20to%20work%20outside%20of%20traditional%20offices%2C%20the%20world's%20best%20talent%20is%20migrating%20from%20superstar%20cities%20like%20New%20York%20and%20London%20to%20places%20like%20Miami%20and%20Dubai.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20leading%20to%20a%20network%20of%20so-called%20%26quot%3Bmeta%20cities%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fhbr.org%2F2023%2F11%2Fthe-rise-of-the-meta-city%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20new%20report%3C%2Fa%3E%20authored%20by%20urban%20planner%20Richard%20Florida%20and%20several%20Boston%20Consulting%20Group%20associates%20in%20the%20Harvard%20Business%20Review.%20Florida%20and%20his%20co-authors%20describe%20meta%20cities%20as%20%26quot%3Ba%20web%20of%20cities%20that%20operate%20as%20a%20distinct%20unit%20and%20are%20attached%20to%20a%20major%20%E2%80%94%20often%20global%20%E2%80%94%20economic%20hub.%26quot%3B%20Rather%20than%20being%20defined%20by%20geography%2C%20a%20meta%20city%20is%20defined%20by%20the%20connections%20between%20hubs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUsing%20LinkedIn%20data%20between%20August%202022%20and%20July%202023%2C%20the%20report%20looked%20particularly%20closely%20at%20the%20talent%20moving%20to%20and%20leaving%20New%20York%2C%20London%2C%20and%20San%20Francisco.%20When%20it%20came%20to%20New%20York%2C%20Miami%20both%20sent%20the%20most%20talent%20and%20received%20the%20most%20talent%20from%20the%20Big%20Apple%2C%20when%20adjusted%20for%20population%20size.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESimilarly%2C%20Austin%2C%20Texas%20received%20more%20talent%20%E2%80%94%20dominated%20by%20tech%20%E2%80%94from%20San%20Francisco%20than%20from%20any%20other%20city.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAustin's%20rise%20is%20best%20understood%20as%20a%20satellite%20of%20San%20Francisco's%20long-established%20tech%20hub%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20authors%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BMiami%20is%20enmeshed%20in%20New%20York%20City's%20finance%20and%20real%20estate%20comple