E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EHis%20significant%20stake%20has%20surged%20in%20value%20to%20around%20%24130%20billion%2C%20marking%20a%20%2444%20billion%20increase%20in%20wealth%20this%20year%20alone%2C%20driven%20by%20a%20remarkable%2056%25%20rise%20in%20Microsoft's%20stock%20price.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3ESteve%20Ballmer's%20passive%20income%20stands%20out%20as%20a%20substantial%20addition%20to%20his%20wealth.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3ESteve%20Ballmer%2C%20who%20joined%20as%20the%2030th%20employee%20in%201980%2C%20amassed%20a%20substantial%20stake.%20He%20became%20Microsoft's%20CEO%20in%202000%2C%20stepping%20down%20in%202014.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EBecause%20of%20the%20stake%20ownership%2C%20Steve%20Ballmer%20is%20close%20to%20becoming%20the%20fourth%20richest%20person%20globally%2C%20just%20a%20few%20billion%20dollars%20shy%20of%20Larry%20Ellison%20and%20his%20former%20boss%2C%20Bill%20Gates.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EIn%202023%2C%20Microsoft%20paid%20%242.79%20per%20share%20in%20dividends%2C%20resulting%20in%20an%20annual%20payment%20of%20around%20%24930%20million%20to%20Mr%20Ballmer%20based%20on%20his%20ownership.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EFor%202024%2C%20Microsoft%20raised%20its%20dividend%20by%2010%25%20to%20%243%20per%20share%2C%20projecting%20a%20potential%20%24999.6%20million%20annual%20dividend%20for%20Mr%20Ballmer.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EWith%20Microsoft%20consistently%20increasing%20its%20dividend%20for%2018%20years%2C%20it%20is%20likely%20Mr%20Ballmer's%20annual%20payout%20will%20surpass%20%241%20billion%20in%202024%20and%20continue%20to%20grow.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EHowever%2C%20Mr%20Ballmer%20is%20also%20likely%20to%20be%20subject%20to%20the%2020%25%20tax%20on%20dividends%20for%20individuals%20earning%20over%20%24500%2C000%20annually.%20This%20implies%20he%20might%20have%20to%20pay%20around%20%242