ring%20a%20CHOGM%20meeting%20in%201983.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20then%20prime%20minister's%20demand%20for%20the%20humble%20papaya%20for%20breakfast%20during%20the%20Commonwealth%20Heads%20of%20Government%20Meeting%20retreat%20sent%20the%20entire%20Taj%20Hotel%20into%20a%20tizzy%2C%20chef%20Satish%20Arora%20recounts%20in%20his%20book%20%26quot%3BSweets%20and%20Bitters%3A%20Tales%20from%20a%20Chef's%20Life%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20a%20%26quot%3Buniquely%20Indian%2C%20very%20local%26quot%3B%20battle%20that%20he%20and%20his%20team%20at%20Taj%20Goa%20were%20fighting%2C%20Mr%20Arora%20writes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20November%201983%20and%20the%20late%20Indira%20Gandhi%20was%20hosting%20high-profile%20leaders%20from%20more%20than%2040%20countries%20for%20a%2048-hour%20retreat%20that%20was%20aiming%20to%20put%20Goa%20on%20the%20world%20tourism%20map.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20was%20a%20flurry%20of%20activity%20--%20roads%20were%20widened%2C%20jetties%20and%20bridges%20built%2C%20street%20lights%20revamped%20and%20the%20airport%20overhauled.%20And%20at%20the%20centre%20of%20it%20all%20was%20the%20hotel%2C%20preparing%20vast%20buffets%20with%20more%20than%20a%20hundred%20dishes.%20In%20the%20midst%20of%20the%20frantic%20activity%20came%20the%20brief%20that%20Indira%20Gandhi%20wanted%20papaya%20for%20breakfast%20every%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhere%20on%20earth%20would%20we%20get%20so%20many%20naturally%20ripened%20papayas%20in%20Goa%20at%20that%20time%20of%20the%20year%3F%20Anticipating%20a%20lack%20of%20consistently%20good%20papayas%20in%20November%2C%20I%20had%20arranged%20for%20raw%20papayas%20to%20be%20brought%20in%20from%20Bombay%20and%20had%20wrapped%20them%20in%20paper%20to%20hasten%20the%20ripening%20the%20process%2C%26quot%3B%20Mr%20Arora%2C%20who%20had%20a%20five-decade%20stint%20at%20the%20Taj%20kitchens%20in%20Mumbai%2C%20says%20in%20the%20book.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20fate%20would%20have%20it%2C%20on%20the%20very%20first%20day%20of%20service%2C%20the%20person%20in-charge%20of%20the%20papayas%20left%20a%20couple%20of%20pieces%20a%20little%20too%20long%20in%20the%20paper%20and%20they%20turned%20squishy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDown%20to%20the%20last%20pieces%20of%20papaya%2C%20the%20staff%20was%20told%20that%20Indira%20Gandhi%20and%20her%20special%20guests%20were%20about%20to%20step%20in%20for%20breakfast.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20%26quot%3Bpanic%26quot%3B%20in%20the%20kitchen%20was%20apparent.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20was%20no%20way%20I%20would%20serve%20overly%20ripe%2C%20soggy%20papaya%20to%20our%20PM%2C%20and%20that%20too%20without%20any%20presentation%20value.%20I%20was%20in%20tears!%26quot%3B%20narrates%20the%20chef.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20followed%20was%20an%20epic%20chase%20to%20procure%20ripe%20papayas%20--%20that%20too%20in%20a%20police%20jeep%20escorted%20by%20men%20in%20uniform.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20police%20jeep%20was%20arranged%20for%20me%20to%20be%20whisked%20off%20to%20the%20nearest%20market%20to%20look%20for%20ripe%20papayas.%20I%20got%20lucky%20and%20picked%20up%20a%20dozen%20pieces%20of%20fruit.%20I%20felt%20like%20a%20warlord%20travelling%20in%20a%20police%20jeep%2C%20being%20escorted%20by%20men%20in%20uniform%2C%20whizzing%20past%20the%20villagers%20with%20my%20twelve%20papayas%20in%20tow%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20recounts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20according%20to%20the%20book%2C%20procuring%20papayas%20was%20only%20half%20the%20battle%20as%20the%20hotel%20security%20and%20members%20of%20the%20Special%20Protection%20Group%20stopped%20Mr%20Arora%20from%20entering%20the%20hotel.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNo%20amount%20of%20explaining%2C%20begging%20and%20pleading%20would%20help%20us%20get%20the%20papayas%20past%20them.%20Finally%2C%20they%20agreed%20to%20let%20the%20papayas%20through%20after%20making%20holes%20in%20each%20of%20them%20to%20check%20for%20explosives.%20I%20was%20disappointed%2C%20but%20we%20used%20our%20skills%20to%20manage%20anyhow%2C%20and%20that%20final%20result%20was%20rewarding%20and%20of%20course%20relieving%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPublished%20by%20Bloomsbury%20India%2C%20%26quot%3BSweets%20and%20Bitters%26quot%3B%2C%20priced%20at%20Rs%20599%2C%20offers%20delicious%20peeks%20into%20the%20most%20well-guarded%20food%20secrets%20of%20celebrities%20and%20heads%20of%20states%2C%20and%20in%20the%20process%20memorialises%20culinary%20milestones%20in%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1703754060000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2020-10%2Fvv0mfv2k_indira-gandhi_625x300_31_October_20.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fwhen-soggy-papayas-for-indira-gandhi-sparked-panic-in-hotel-book-4756916%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20then%20prime%20minister's%20demand%20for%20the%20humble%20papaya%20for%20breakfast%20during%20the%20Commonwealth%20Heads%20of%20Government%20Meeting%20retreat%20sent%20the%20entire%20Taj%20Hotel%20into%20a%20tizzy%2C%20chef%20Satish%20Arora%20recounts%20in%20his%20book.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A3%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fwhen-soggy-papayas-for-indira-gandhi-sparked-panic-in-hotel-book-4756916%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fwhen-soggy-papayas-for-indira-gandhi-sparked-panic-in-hotel-book-4756916%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fwhen-soggy-papayas-for-indira-gandhi-sparked-panic-in-hotel-book-4756916%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22'India%20seeks%20extradition%20of%2026%2F11%20mastermind%20Hafiz%20Saeed'%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1703753996000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fp