cs%2Fcpim-turns-down-ram-temple-invite-says-religion-shouldnt-be-used-for-political-gain%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edeclined%20the%20invitation%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20saying%20religion%20is%20a%20personal%20choice%20and%20should%20not%20to%20be%20converted%20into%20an%20instrument%20for%20political%20gain.%20But%20senior%20Congress%20leader%20Digvijay%20Singh%2C%20who%20is%20regarded%20by%20many%20as%20uncompromisingly%20anti-communal%20in%20his%20politics%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fshe-will-go-or-congress-leader-on-ayodhya-invite-for-sonia-gandhi-4716525%5C%22%3Econfirmed%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20Gandhi%20is%20considering%20this%20invitation%20%E2%80%9Cpositively%E2%80%9D.%20It%20was%20also%20said%20that%20either%20Gandhi%20herself%20would%20go%20or%20a%20delegation%20of%20the%20party%20would%20attend%20the%20Ram%20Mandir%20consecration%20ceremony.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EResponding%20to%20questions%20over%20his%20invitation%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.financialexpress.com%2Findia-news%2Fshe-is-very-positive-sonia-gandhi-likely-to-attend-ram-mandir-consecration-ceremony-says-digvijaya-singh%2F3344574%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESingh%20said%20sarcastically%20that%20he%20was%20not%20invited%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%E2%80%9CThey%20will%20not%20invite%20me%20because%20they%20are%20not%20inviting%20the%20true%20devotees.%20Whether%20it%20be%20Murli%20Manohar%20Joshi%2C%20Lal%20Krishna%20Advani%20or%20Digvijay%20Singh%2C%20they%20will%20not%20be%20given%20the%20invitation.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20what%20Singh%20is%20saying%20has%20been%20reported%20correctly%2C%20then%20the%20Congress%20party%20is%20going%20to%20make%20another%20suicidal%20blunder.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20was%20to%20open%20the%20locks%20of%20the%20Babri%20Masjid%20in%201986%20under%20the%20supervision%20of%20its%20state%20government%20in%20Uttar%20Pradesh.%20There%20is%20a%20gap%20of%20only%20six%20years%20between%20that%20decision%20and%20the%20demolition%20of%20the%20Babri%20Masjid.%20Actually%2C%20it%20should%20be%20said%20that%20this%20was%20the%20party%E2%80%99s%20second%20blunder.%20The%20first%2C%20in%20fact%2C%20was%20made%20by%20its%20state%20government%20in%201949%20when%20it%20ignored%20the%20crime%20committed%20by%20%E2%80%98unknown%20persons%E2%80%99%20of%20surreptitiously%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcommunalism%2Funtold-story-rama-idol-surfaced-inside-babri-masjid%5C%22%3Eplacing%20some%20idols%20in%20the%20Babri%20Masjid.%3C%2Fa%3E%20Rather%20than%20taking%20remedial%20stepts%2C%20the%20government%20decided%20to%20lock%20the%20Babri%20Masjid%20and%20ban%20the%20entry%20of%20Muslims%20into%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20took%2037%20years%20to%20from%20the%20locking%20of%201949%20to%20the%20unlocking%20of%201986%20but%20only%20six%20years%20to%20go%20from%201986%20to%20the%20demolition%20of%201992.%20One%20crime%20led%20to%20another.%20Once%20again%2C%20the%20Congress%2C%20which%20was%20in%20power%20in%20New%20Delhi%2C%20felt%20it%20had%20no%20option%20but%20to%20live%20with%20this%20crime.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESmuggling%20idols%20of%20Hindu%20gods%20and%20goddesses%20into%20the%20Babri%20Masjid%20in%20the%20middle%20of%20the%20night%20in%201949%20was%20a%20crime%20and%20the%20demolition%20of%20the%20Babri%20Masjid%20in%20broad%20daylight%20on%20December%206%2C%201992%2C%20under%20the%20protection%20of%20the%20state%20government%20and%20inaction%20of%20the%20Union%20government%20was%20also%20a%20crime.%20Both%20these%20acts%20were%20declared%20crimes%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court.%20It%20is%20a%20different%20matter%20that%20the%20same%20Supreme%20Court%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fayodhya-verdict-supreme-court-judgment%5C%22%3Eallowed%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20proceeds%20%E2%80%93%C2%A0%20the%20land%20on%20which%20the%20Babri%20Masjid%20stood%20%E2%80%93%20to%20be%20enjoyed%20by%20those%20who%20were%20involved%20in%20both%20these%20crimes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202019%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20ordered%20the%20government%20to%20build%20a%20Ram%20temple%20on%20the%20land%20that%20became%20vacant%20by%20obliterating%20the%20Babri%20Masjid%20through%20acts%20of%20crimes%20and%20fraud.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENo%20member%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20bench%20which%20gave%20this%20decision%20had%20the%20courage%20to%20take%20responsibility%20for%20the%20judicial%20acrobatics%20this%20involved.%20The%20Ayodhya%20judgment%20is%20one%20of%20the%20rare%20court%20decisions%20in%20which%20the%20judge%20who%20wrote%20the%20decision%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Ftop-stories%2Fwho-is-the-author-of-ayodhya-judgment-149644%5C%22%3Edid%20not%20want%20his%20name%20recorded.%3C%2Fa%3E%20This%20was%20not%20humility%2C%20this%20was%20cowardice.%20No%20judge%20wanted%20to%20be%20remembered%20as%20the%20author%20of%20this%20judgment%20that%20turned%20morality%20on%20its%20head.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20all%2C%20the%20bench%20itself%20had%20concluded%20(1)%20that%20the%20Babri%20Masjid%20had%20been%20standing%20at%20that%20site%20for%20more%20than%20500%20years%2C%20(2)%20that%20there%20was%20no%20evidence%20that%20the%20mosque%20was%20built%20by%20demolishing%20any%20temple%20and%20(3)%20that%20Muslims%20used%20to%20worship%20in%20it%20till%201949%2C%20when%20the%20idols%20of%20Hindu%20gods%20and%20goddesses%20were%20smuggled%20into%20it%2C%20which%20was%20called%20a%20crime.%20The%20court%20was%20also%20unambiguous%20that%20it%20was%20an%20egregious%20crime%20to%20demolish%20the%20masjid%20on%20December%206%2C%201992.%20Having%20said%20all%20this%2C%20the%20logical%20decision%20would%20have%20been%20to%20order%20the%20reconstruction%20of%20the%20criminally%20demolished%20mosque%20at%20the%20site%20where%20it%20had%20stood%20for%20centuries.%20But%20no%2C%20the%20court%20decided%20that%20since%20some%20Hindus%20had%20been%20looking%20at%20it%20with%20longing%20for%20years%2C%20this%20land%20should%20be%20given%20to%20them%20to%20build%20a%20Ram%20temple.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELeaving%20aside%20the%20court%E2%80%99s%20deeply%20flawed%20legal%20reasoning%2C%20it%20is%20worth%20asking%20whether%20any%20sacred%20feeling%20can%20truly%20arise%20on%20a%20piece%20of%20land%20acquired%20through%20crime%2C%20cowardice%2C%20and%20cunning.%20Surely%2C%20it%20is%20impossible%20for%20the%20Ram%20temple%20which%20is%20going%20to%20be%20inaugurated%20on%20January%2022%2C%202024%20to%20be%20free%20from%20the%20memory%20of%20the%20evil%20human%20acts%20that%20led%20to%20its%20construction.%20It%20is%20certainly%20not%20a%20place%20that%20can%20give%20a%20devotee%20spiritual%20peace.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20purpose%20of%20this%20Ram%20temple%20is%20neither%20religious%20nor%20spiritual.%20That%20much%20was%20made%20clear%20by%20the%20general%20secretary%20of%20the%20Ram%20Mandir%20Trust%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.telegraphindia.com%2Findia%2Fall-star-pitch-to-temple-opener-vishwa-hindu-parishad-vice-president-says-event-on-par-with-independence-day%2Fcid%2F1989012%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ein%20recent%20comments%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0Champat%20Rai%20said%20that%20the%20date%20of%20January%2022%20is%20as%20important%20as%20that%20of%20August%2015%2C%201947.%20%E2%80%9CThis%20day%20is%20also%20as%20important%20as%201971%2C%20when%20about%20one%20lakh%20Pakistani%20soldiers%20surrendered%20before%20our%20army.%20This%20day%20is%20on%20a%20par%20with%20the%20day%20our%20country%20reclaimed%20its%20right%20over%20Kargil%20in%201999%2C%E2%80%9D%20Rai%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20not%20difficult%20to%20decipher%20his%20intent%20behind%20the%20mention%20of%20two%20incidents%20involving%20Pakistan%20and%20its%20defeat%20in%20battle.%20But%20it%20is%20Rai%E2%80%99s%20comparison%20of%20January%2022%20with%20India%E2%80%99s%20independence%20day%20that%20bears%20closer%20scrutiny.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAugust%2015%2C%201947%20is%20a%20day%20that%20evokes%20a%20feeling%20of%20freedom%20%E2%80%93%20a%20freedom%20achieved%20without%20any%20lies%20or%20deception.%20In%20the%20freedom%20struggle%2C%20the%20fight%20against%20the%20once%20more%20powerful%20Britain%20was%20conducted%20openly.%20Gandhi%20and%20his%20associates%20fought%20their%20battles%20with%20the%20British%20face%20to%20face.%20There%20was%20no%20conspiracy%2C%20no%20violence%20from%20the%20Indian%20side.%20There%20was%20something%20deeply%20moral%20about%20the%20victory%20of%20August%2015%2C%20which%20compelled%20even%20the%20enemy%20Britain%20to%20surrender.%20This%20struggle%20was%20not%20driven%20by%20hatred.%20It%20generated%20love%20and%20compassion.%20And%20that%20is%20why%2C%20all%20the%20oppressed%20people%20of%20the%20world%20took%20inspiration%20from%20this%20great%20battle.%20In%20stark%20contrast%20to%20this%2C%20the%20new%20Ram%20temple%20coming%20up%20at%20Ayodhya%20would%20not%20have%20been%20possible%20without%20deceit%2C%20lies%2C%20and%20violence%2C%20as%20well%20as%20cowardice.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F07%2F19130137%2Fadmin-ajax-1.v1.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F07%2F19130137%2Fadmin-ajax-1.v1.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F07%2F19130137%2Fadmin-ajax-1.v1-300x205.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F07%2F19130137%2Fadmin-ajax-1.v1-1024x699.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-381392%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22819%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EThe%20demolition%20of%20the%20Babri%20Masjid%20in%201992.%20Photo%3A%20Sanjay%20Sharma%2FINDIAPIX%20NETWORK%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20protector%20of%20Ram%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20being%20announced%20that%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20has%20ended%20Ram%E2%80%99s%20exile%20and%20has%20brought%20him%20back%20to%20Ayodhya.%20An%20organisation%20that%20believes%20in%20violence%20and%20hatred%20has%20declared%20itself%20the%20guardian%20of%20Ram.%20The%20temple%2C%20which%20is%20going%20to%20be%20inaugurated%20on%20January%2022%2C%20is%20of%20a%20Ram%20whose%20guardian%20or%20patron%20is%20the%20BJP%20and%20the%20Rashtriya%20Swayamsevak%20Sangh%3Cem%3E%20(%3C%2Fem%3ERSS).%20If%20Hindus%20recognise%20this%20temple%2C%20it%20would%20mean%20that%20the%20BJP%20or%20the%20RSS%20are%20going%20to%20determine%20their%20religion%20and%20their%20religious%20conduct%20in%20the%20days%20and%20years%20ahead.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20temple%20would%20not%20have%20been%20possible%20without%20the%20campaign%20led%20by%20Lal%20Krishna%20Advani.%20He%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hindustantimes.com%2Findia-news%2Fwhat-lk-advani-who-is-likely-to-skip-ayodhya-event-has-said-about-ram-temple-a-flashback-101702978734825.html%23%3A~%3Atext%3DIn%2520a%2520statement%2520in%25202004%2Cdebate%2520on%2520secularism%2520in%2520India.%2522%5C%22%3Ehas%20admitted%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%3Cem%3E%20Ramjanmabhoomi%3C%2Fem%3E%20campaign%20was%20actually%20a%20political%20campaign%2C%20and%20that%20its%20purpose%20was%20not%20religious%20or%20spiritual%20at%20all.%20Ram%20was%20just%20an%20instrument%20for%20the%20RSS%20to%20capture%20the%20minds%20of%20Hindus.%20This%20is%20clear%20from%20Advani%E2%80%99s%20confession%20that%20he%20was%20not%20fighting%20for%20Hinduism.%20It%20was%20to%20somehow%20convince%20the%20Hindus%20that%20only%20the%20BJP%20cared%20for%20their%20Ram%20and%20to%20use%20that%20feeling%20to%20build%20their%20support%20base.%20Clearly%2C%20the%20party%20has%20succeeded%20in%20doing%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20was%20violence%20at%20every%20stage%20of%20the%20campaign%20to%20demolish%20the%20Babri%20Masjid.%20The%20Toyota%20truck%20with%20which%20Advani%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fthe-ayodhya-ram-temple-and-lk-advanis-sour-grapes-of-rath%5C%22%3Estarted%20his%20unholy%20journey%20%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0spawned%20a%20bloodbath%20in%20north%20India.%20The%20blood%20that%20was%20shed%20in%20this%20entire%20campaign%20has%20not%20been%20accounted%20for%20till%20date.%20Who%20was%20responsible%20for%20that%3F%20Not%20Ram%20but%20the%20BJP%2C%20for%20whom%20Ram%20was%20just%20a%20politically%20expedient%20name.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20time%2C%20too%2C%20Ram%20is%20only%20a%20means.%20As%20the%20main%20%3Cem%3Eyajman%3C%2Fem%3E%20or%20main%20%3Cem%3Ehota%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0of%20this%20latest%20Ram%20temple%20%3Cem%3Eyagya%3C%2Fem%3E%20in%20Ayodhya%2C%20a%20person%20has%20been%20chosen%20whose%20life%20is%20made%20up%20of%20false%20words%2C%20false%20conduct%2C%20propagation%20of%20hatred%20and%20violence.%20What%20sacred%20spirit%20would%20this%20%3Cem%3Eyagya%3C%2Fem%3E%20evoke%3F%20Whoever%20participates%20in%20this%20%3Cem%3Eyagya%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0%20%E2%80%93organised%20by%20those%20for%20whom%20Ram%20is%20an%20instrument%20and%20presided%20over%20by%20a%20man%20who%20is%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fnarendra-modis-personality-has-no-place-for-compromise-or-repentance%5C%22%3Epathological%20liar%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0%E2%80%93%20legitimises%20untruth%20and%20violence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20not%20possible%20to%20separate%20the%20land%20where%20the%20temple%20has%20been%20built%20from%20the%20falsehood%2C%20deceit%2C%20violence%20and%20cowardice%20with%20which%20it%20was%20eventually%20acquired.%20Does%20any%20political%20party%20now%20have%20the%20courage%20to%20say%20this%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20needs%20to%20have%20a%20national%20day%20of%20collective%20repentance.%20A%20day%20of%20atonement%20for%20the%20sin%20committed%20in%20the%20name%20of%20Ram.%20Most%20of%20all%20for%20the%20Congress%20party%20but%20also%20for%20other%20political%20parties.%20After%20all%2C%20without%20the%20cowardice%20of%20the%20Congress%2C%20this%20temple%20could%20not%20have%20been%20built.%20The%20Congress%20members%20were%20right%20when%20they%20claimed%20that%20without%20them%20this%20temple%20would%20not%20have%20been%20possible.%20But%20this%20is%20not%20a%20matter%20of%20pride%2C%20but%20of%20shame.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Congress%20should%20not%20forget%20that%20the%20conspiracy%20to%20render%20August%2015%2C%201947%20meaningless%20had%20started%20from%20that%20very%20moment.%20Now%2C%20a%20claim%20is%20being%20made%20about%20the%20parity%20of%20January%2022%2C%202024%20with%20August%2015%2C%201947.%20Can%20the%20Congress%20realise%20that%20it%20was%20its%20reluctance%20to%20confront%20communal%20deceit%20and%20violence%20that%20has%20brought%20the%20country%20to%20this%20state%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F08%2F07083139%2F2020_8img05_Aug_2020_PTI05-08-2020_000172B.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F08%2F07083139%2F2020_8img05_Aug_2020_PTI05-08-2020_000172B.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F08%2F07083139%2F2020_8img05_Aug_2020_PTI05-08-2020_000172B-300x190.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F08%2F07083139%2F2020_8img05_Aug_2020_PTI05-08-2020_000172B-1024x649.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-471716%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22761%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EPM%20Narendra%20Modi%20takes%20part%20in%20the%20bhoomi%20pujan%20for%20the%20construction%20of%20a%20Ram%20temple%20in%20Ayodhya%2C%20August%205%2C%202020.%20Photo%3A%20PIB%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Congress%20can%20repent.%20It%20can%20respond%20to%20the%20invitation%20by%20saying%20that%20for%20the%20party%20of%20Gandhi%20and%20Nehru%2C%20this%20is%20a%20moment%20of%20introspection.%20A%20moment%20to%20solidify%20its%20reluctant%20secularism.%20It%20should%20muster%20the%20courage%20to%20say%20that%20India%20is%20still%20suffering%20the%20consequences%20of%20not%20punishing%20the%20crimes%20committed%20in%201949%20and%201992%20in%20the%20context%20of%20the%20Babri%20Masjid.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20repentance%20is%20also%20essential%20for%20the%20self-redemption%20of%20Hindu%20society.%20That%20it%20will%20not%20repent%20is%20a%20sad%20truth%2C%20but%20it%20is%20also%20true%20that%20this%20refusal%20to%20make%20a%20reckoning%20with%20its%20past%20will%20only%20make%20it%20look%20worse.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20my%20friends%2C%20in%20sharp%20contrast%20to%20the%20Congress%E2%80%99s%20leaders%2C%20said%20that%20after%20November%202019%2C%20he%20stopped%20going%20to%20Ayodhya.%20Before%20that%20he%20used%20to%20visit%20Ayodhya%20frequently.%20He%20used%20to%20take%20holy%20baths%20in%20the%20Sarayu%20river%2C%20visit%20Hanuman%20Garhi%20and%20Kanak%20Bhawan.%20He%20narrated%20an%20incident%20of%20his%20visit%20or%20%3Cem%3Edarshan%3C%2Fem%3E%20to%20Ayodhya.%20He%20asked%20an%20old%20sadhu%20what%20was%20sacred%20in%20Ayodhya.%20The%20sadhu%20said%20that%20firstly%2C%20it%20was%20Sarayu%2C%20which%20was%20eternal%2C%20and%20second%20it%20was%20the%20land%20of%20Ayodhya.%20Everything%20else%20is%20only%20a%20claim%20made%20by%20mortals.%20And%20these%20are%20not%20claims%20of%20devotion%20towards%20Ram%2C%20but%20claims%20of%20their%20own%20ownership%20of%20worldly%20possessions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20my%20friend%20started%20coming%20to%20Ayodhya%2C%20the%20debris%20of%20the%20Babri%20Masjid%20was%20still%20there.%20A%20witness%20to%20a%20planned%20crime.%20A%20crime%20in%20which%20nearly%20all%20institutions%20of%20the%20state%20participated%20or%20collaborated.%20He%20never%20ever%20thought%20of%20visiting%20this%20so-called%20%3Cem%3ERamjanmabhoomi%3C%2Fem%3E%20which%20was%20claimed%20to%20be%20the%20very%20spot%20on%20which%20the%20Babri%20mosque%20stood.%20In%20this%20debris%20was%20a%20hope%20that%20perhaps%20India%20would%20recognise%20the%20injustice%20done%20on%20December%206%2C%201992.%20But%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fayodhya-judgment-india-enveloping-darkness%5C%22%3ENovember%209%2C%202019%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20this%20hope%20of%20justice%20was%20buried%20very%20deep%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court.%20From%20November%209%2C%202019%20Ayodhya%20became%20a%20symbol%20of%20injustice.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMy%20friend%20said%20that%20from%20that%20day%2C%20Ayodhya%20disappeared%20from%20his%20mind.%20It%20is%20now%20a%20broken%20idol%2C%20a%20%3Cem%3Ekhandit%20pratima%3C%2Fem%3E.%20It%20is%20not%20possible%20to%20worship%20there.%20It%20is%20a%20symbol%20of%20the%20victory%20of%20injustice.%20There%20is%20no%20relation%20between%20injustice%20and%20spirituality.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20only%20the%20Congress%20party%20could%20express%20this%20sentiment.%20Even%20if%20it%20chooses%20to%20remain%20absent%20from%20celebrating%20the%20victory%20of%20this%20power%20without%20commenting%2C%20it%20would%20still%20be%20neglecting%20its%20duty.%20That%20duty%20is%20to%20awaken%20a%20sense%20of%20right%20and%20wrong%20among%20the%20people.%20If%20my%20young%20Hindu%20friend%20still%20holds%20that%20awareness%20in%20mind%2C%20there%20is%20no%20reason%20why%20it%20cannot%20be%20stirred%20in%20others.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1703683398000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F05%2F08195755%2FFvdM0YTWwAASRHL.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%